{
  "doc_id": "8413",
  "text": "With the recognition of sublethal stress, efforts have been directed toward development of enumeration procedures which retain selectivity for fecal coliforms but allow recovery of stressed cells. Stuart et al. [CITATION_1] developed a bilayer plate containing both a selective and a nonselective medium for recovery of fecal coliforms stressed by the aquatic environment. Speck et al. [CITATION_2] developed a similar bilayer plating procedure for enumerating injured coliforms in frozen foods.",
